---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import DisclaimerBox from '../components/DisclaimerBox.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About Honestly Profitable"
  description="Honestly Profitable is an independent business reference: real startup costs, realistic earnings, and straight talk about difficulty and failure — no courses to sell, no affiliate pressure, and advertising kept fully separate from our content."
  path="/about"
>
  <div class="container container-narrow page-head">
    <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'Home', href: '/' }, { label: 'About' }]} />
    <h1>About Honestly Profitable</h1>
    <p class="lead">A serious, independent reference for anyone genuinely weighing whether — and how — to start a business.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="container container-narrow page-body">
    <h2>Why this site exists</h2>
    <p>
      Most "business ideas" content online is built to sell you something — a course, a coaching
      program, an affiliate link, or a dream. The numbers are cherry-picked, the failures are
      hidden, and the hard parts are glossed over. We built {SITE.name} to be the opposite: a
      practical, honest reference that respects your intelligence and your real circumstances.
    </p>
    <p>
      Every business we cover gets the same honest treatment — what it actually costs to start,
      what it realistically earns (broken into beginner, experienced, and top-earner ranges), how
      long it really takes to see income, what skills it truly requires, and what most people get
      wrong when they try it. We show the full realistic range, not the best case. If a business is
      hard, capital-intensive, heavily regulated, or fails often, we say so plainly.
    </p>

    <h2>What we cover</h2>
    <p>
      The site is a growing library of hundreds of in-depth business breakdowns across 14 categories
      — service businesses, trades, food and beverage, retail, online and technology, health and
      wellness, real estate, automotive, education and coaching, events, pets, and more. Each
      breakdown is a full page with itemized startup costs, honest earnings ranges, a step-by-step
      start plan, the skills required, common mistakes, how to find customers, how the business
      scales, and a candid "is this right for you?" checklist.
    </p>

    <h2>What makes us different</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Real startup costs</strong> — itemized and realistic, not estimates pulled from thin air.</li>
      <li><strong>Realistic earnings</strong> — based on reported data and operator accounts, separated into beginner, experienced, and top-earner outcomes rather than a single best-case number.</li>
      <li><strong>Honest failure analysis</strong> — what goes wrong, why people quit, and how to avoid it.</li>
      <li><strong>No courses to sell</strong> — no upsells, no affiliate pressure, no "secret system."</li>
      <li><strong>Written for real constraints</strong> — real budgets, real time, real skills, real regulations.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Who is behind Honestly Profitable</h2>
    <p>
      {SITE.name} is produced by an independent editorial team of writers and researchers who study
      each business model using public data, industry reports, cost guides, and first-hand operator
      accounts. We are not affiliated with any of the businesses, franchises, courses, or tools
      mentioned on the site, and no business pays to be included, ranked higher, or described more
      favorably. Our detailed process is documented in
      <a href="/how-we-research-businesses">how we research businesses</a>,
      <a href="/data-sources">data sources</a>, and our
      <a href="/editorial-standards">editorial standards</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Editorial independence</h2>
    <p>
      Our only obligation is to the reader making a real decision. Advertising and any commercial
      relationship are kept strictly separate from our research: advertisers have no influence over
      which businesses we cover or what we say about them, ads are clearly labeled, and they are never
      placed inside the Business Finder or next to the cost and earnings figures where they could
      confuse a financial decision.
    </p>

    <h2>How we make money</h2>
    <p>
      We believe in being transparent about this. {SITE.name} is supported by advertising. We may
      display ads from advertising networks (such as Google AdSense) to keep the site free and
      independent. Ads are clearly labeled, kept away from the data and tools, and never disguised as
      recommendations. We do not sell courses, and our business breakdowns are not influenced by
      advertisers. See our <a href="/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a> for how advertising cookies
      work and how to opt out.
    </p>

    <h2>How to use the site</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Not sure where to start?</strong> The <a href="/find-my-business">Business Finder</a> asks a few honest questions and matches you to businesses that fit your real budget, time, and skills — entirely in your browser, with nothing stored.</li>
      <li><strong>Have a direction in mind?</strong> Browse <a href="/businesses">all businesses</a> by category, or filter by budget, skill, or time commitment.</li>
      <li><strong>Comparing options?</strong> Each page's numbers and "is this right for you?" checklist are built to help you rule things in or out honestly.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Our standard</h2>
    <p>
      The measure of success for any page on this site is simple: when you finish reading, you
      should be able to say, "Now I actually know whether this is right for me, and exactly what I
      need to do to start." Everything we publish is built toward that moment.
    </p>

    <h2>Corrections and contact</h2>
    <p>
      Accuracy is the entire point of the site. If you spot a number that looks wrong or out of date
      — especially if you operate one of these businesses — please tell us via the
      <a href="/contact">contact page</a>. We take corrections seriously and update pages when a
      credible issue is raised.
    </p>

    <div style="margin-top: 2rem;">
      <DisclaimerBox />
    </div>

    <p class="page-updated">Last updated: July 2026 · {SITE.domain}</p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
